17/02/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbia's re-elected president Boris Tadic was sworn in on Friday (February 15th), beginning his second five-year term in the post.
"I swear that I will dedicate all my powers to keep the sovereignty and territorial integrity of Serbia, including Kosovo as its integral part, as well as to protect human and minority rights and freedoms," Tadic told parliament.
He reiterated in his oath that he would never give up Kosovo and vowed to exert all his efforts to help Serbia become an EU member.
(Tanjug, Beta, UPI, DPA, Xinhua - 15/02/08)
